  "texts": [
    "Next, we consider the map φ: [0, 1] → [0, 1] that maps an arbitrary position x L into the comple-mentary best-response position 1 -x BR R, where x BR R solves the following (with x L taken as given):",
    "Utility U R is quasi-concave when H is symmetric, so it must be the case that this admits a unique",
    "x * R (x L) which is a global maximum for U R over all of [0, 1] (see Mas-Colell et al. (1995)).",
    "Moreover, by the inverse function theorem, the solution x * R (x L) is continuous in x L.",
    "By Brouwer's theorem, there exists a fixed point of φ such that x * R = x BR R (1 -x * R), which by symmetry implies that x * L = x BR L (x * R), and thus (x * L, x * R) is an anti-symmetric Nash equilibrium by construction."
  ],
